HEADWORD: Pharmacodymanics
<hw>Phar`ma*co*dy*man"ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>fa`rmakon</grk> medicine + E. <ets>dynamics</ets>.]</ety> <def>That
branch of pharmacology which treats of the action and the effects of
medicines in the body, and also their distribution in various bodily
tissues over time, and their breakdown and excretion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

